reviews.review_text: Best SBD This is the best sbd out there of this show.There is one more out there thats pretty good but you can hear the crowd but its not like an Audience recording its like the audience got mixed into the sbd or somthing I think it just got toned out but its a real good job.But some dont like the audience in there show even if it sounds realy good.Im just letting ya all know.But I give this sbd 5 for sound and still a 4 for the show

Nice for 1994 Great sounding SBD and quite well-played show. Sloppy start of the set one and only after Mexicali band finally fired up. After this it was a great pleasure to listen to the music and of course there were some interesting surprises during second set.

Corrina is a blast with powerful bass lines and nice guitar solos. Before this warm and inspired version of UJB ended with nice Supplication tease and of course don't forget about the highlight of the concert what is notorious for being one of the biggest letdowns of the era: instead of Cosmic Charlie which seemed imminent Jerry turns to Wharf Rat. Being a fan of this song I won't grumble. 

Turn on Your Lovelight and Rain were great pieces to finish the show.

Cosmic Charlie Miller I was sitting right next to my friend Mr. Miller for this show. Right over that right side back entrance over the floor. The Cosmic tease hands down the cruelest thing Jerry ever did. Never will I forget giving Charlie high fives and hugs then seeing his face as it became Wharf Rat. " I'm outta here" is all he could say.

I am on an amazing journey I am listening to every 1994 show in order, mining for gold. 

Well played show here, with a fantastic Cosmic Charlie Tease>Wharf Rat.
